      "message": "Shell-quoting bug. The \\\" at the end is inside a single-quoted bash string, so the backslash is emitted literally.\n\nLooks like it was copied from the Groovy version, where \\\" is a valid Groovy GString escape — but bash single quotes don\u0027t process escapes, so the backslash needs to go.\n\nThe resulting line in `plugins/external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel` is `include(\"//plugins/\u003cname\u003e:external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel\\\")` — Starlark treats \\\" as an escaped quote and never closes the string, so Bazel will fail to parse the file.\n\n```suggestion\n    echo \u0027include(\"//plugins/\u0027$pluginName\u0027:external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel\")\u0027 \u003e\u003e plugins/external_plugin_deps.MODULE.bazel\n```",
